          <h2 class="details-title">Mahabaleshwar: The Queen of Hill Stations in Maharashtra</h2>
          <p>
            estled in the Western Ghats, Mahabaleshwar, located in the Satara district of Maharashtra, is a picturesque
            hill station and a popular getaway for nature lovers and adventure enthusiasts. Famous for its lush
            greenery, cascading waterfalls, serene lakes, and stunning viewpoints, Mahabaleshwar is also known for its
            delicious strawberries and historical significance.
          </p>
          <h5>A Glimpse into History</h5>
          <p>Mahabaleshwar’s name is derived from the Mahabali temple dedicated to Lord Shiva. Historically, it was a
            summer retreat during British rule and served as the capital of the Bombay Presidency. Today, it stands as a
            perfect blend of natural beauty and cultural heritage.</p>
          <h5>Top Attractions in Mahabaleshwar</h5>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>Arthur’s Seat</strong>:
              <p>Known as the "Queen of all points," Arthur’s Seat offers panoramic views of the deep valleys and the
                Savitri River. It is one of the most famous viewpoints in Mahabaleshwar, ideal for photography and
                peaceful contemplation.</p>
              <br>
              <img style="max-width: 100%;max-height: 400px;"
                src="https://www.trawell.in/admin/images/upload/162482708Mahabaleshwar_Arthur_%20Seat_Point_Main.jpg">
            </li>
            <li><strong>Venna Lake</strong>:
              <p>This serene lake is a hub for boating, horse riding, and picnics. Surrounded by lush greenery, it is a
                must-visit spot for families and couples.</p>
              <br>
              <img style="max-width: 100%;max-height: 400px;"
                src="https://images.jdmagicbox.com/comp/mahabaleshwar/y1/9999p2168.2168.141212110055.q9y1/catalogue/venna-lake-mahabaleshwar-ho-mahabaleshwar-tourist-attraction-i986qsf4qv.jpg">
            </li>
            <li><strong>Pratapgad Fort</strong>:
              <p>Located about 20 kilometers from Mahabaleshwar, Pratapgad Fort is a historical marvel built by
                Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj. The fort offers insights into Maratha history and stunning views of the
                surrounding hills..</p>
              <br>
              <img style="max-width: 100%;max-height: 400px;"
                src="https://s7ap1.scene7.com/is/image/incredibleindia/pratapgarh-fort-mahabaleshwar-maharashtra-1-attr-hero?qlt=82&ts=1726668891652">
            </li>
            <li><strong>Elephant’s Head Point</strong>:
              <p>Shaped like an elephant's head and trunk, this point provides breathtaking views of the Sahyadri hills
                and is a favorite spot for nature enthusiasts.</p>
              <br>
