            </li>
            <li><strong>Mapro Garden</strong>:
              <p>A paradise for strawberry lovers, Mapro Garden offers an array of strawberry-based products, fresh
                juices, and ice creams. The garden also hosts the annual Strawberry Festival, attracting thousands of
                visitors.</p>
              <br>
              <img style="max-width: 100%;max-height: 400px;"
                src="https://mahabaleshwartourism.in/images/places-to-visit/headers/mapro-garden-mahabaleshwar-tourism-entry-fee-timings-holidays-reviews-header.jpg">
            </li>
            <li><strong>Mahabaleshwar Temple</strong>:
              <p>Dedicated to Lord Shiva, the Mahabaleshwar Temple is an ancient and sacred site. The temple is known
                for its swayambhu lingam (self-originated lingam) and draws devotees from far and wide.</p>
              <br>
              <img style="max-width: 100%;max-height: 400px;"
                src="https://www.holidify.com/images/cmsuploads/compressed/shutterstock_1333770320_20200223204952.jpg">
            </li>
            <li><strong>Lingmala Waterfall</strong>:
              <p>A mesmerizing cascade surrounded by dense forests, Lingmala Waterfall is a great spot for trekking and
                photography. It is particularly stunning during the monsoon season.</p>
              <br>
              <img style="max-width: 100%;max-height: 400px;"
                src="https://hoteldreamland.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lingmala-waterfall.jpg">
            </li>
            <li><strong>Wilson Point</strong>:
              <p>Also known as Sunrise Point, Wilson Point is the highest point in Mahabaleshwar and offers captivating
                views of the sunrise and the surrounding landscape.</p>
              <br>
              <img style="max-width: 100%;max-height: 400px;"
                src="https://mahabaleshwartourism.in/images/places-to-visit/headers/wilson-point-sunrise-point-mahabaleshwar-tourism-entry-fee-timings-holidays-reviews-header.jpg">
            </li>
          </ol>
          <h5>Activities to Enjoy</h5>
          <ul>
            <li>Summer (March to June): Perfect for escaping the heat and enjoying cool weather.</li>
            <li>Monsoon (July to September): Witness lush greenery and flowing waterfalls, though heavy rainfall can
              restrict outdoor activities.</li>
            <li>Winter (October to February): Ideal for a cozy getaway, with chilly weather and clear skies.</li>
          </ul>
          <h5>Tips for Travelers</h5>
          <ul>
            <li>Pack warm clothing as the weather can be cool, especially in the evenings.</li>
            <li>Plan your visit to avoid peak holiday seasons if you prefer a quieter experience.</li>
            <li>Carry comfortable footwear for walking and trekking.</li>
          </ul>
